<div class="container">
	<h2>Dashboard</h2>
	<p>Welcome to HostControl, a web interface for managing servers for web-based hosting. The features available are as follows.</p>


    <h4>Websites</h4>
    <p>Setup virtualhosts so your server can handle domains. You can setup new websites, manage SSL certificates, and access files quickly for each site from the websites interface.</p>
    
    <h4>Databases</h4>
    <p>From the databases panel, you can manage databases, manage data users, and provide database access. There is also a link to the phpMyAdmin interface for convenience.</p>
    
    <h4>DNS Records</h4>
    <p>Add new domains from the DNS Records interface. By default only an SOA will be setup, you will need to create the additional records after adding a domain.</p>
    
    <h4>Email</h4>
    <p>Add a domain and an email account to begin receiving email on this server. There is also a link to the Roundcube webmail client from this interface.</p>
    
    <h4>FTP Users</h4>
    <p>When you need to give a developer access to your files, setup an FTP user for them with the FTP users interface.</p>
    
    <h4>File Manager</h4>
    <p>Manage any of your files in your home directory for the user you are logged in as.</p>
    
    <h4>Firewall</h4>
    <p>Not yet implemented</p>
    
    <h4>Console</h4>
    <p>Use a web based SSH connection to handle your business.</p>
    
    <h4>Services</h4>
    <p>Not yet implemented</p>
    
    <h4>Users</h4>
    <p>Create system users that can maintain their own services.</p>
    
    <h4>Settings</h4>
    <p>Change your password, create API tokens, and view a full API feature list.</p>
	
